
--FLASK
Flask is a micro framework licensed under a three clause BSD License. A BSD license gives consent to anyone to do what needs to be done as long as the copyright in Flask sticks around, the conditions are not modified and the disclaimer is present. Furthermore you must not use the names of the authors to promote derivatives of the software without written consent.

It uses a nifty Python feaure that allow for wrappers and decorators. 

In the the box with Flask you get:
	development server and debugger
	integrated unit testing support
	RESTful request dispatching
	uses jinja 2 for templeting
	support for secure cookies (client side)
	WSGI compliant
	unicode based
	documented really well